DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/S0022-1996(01)00153-2
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0022199601001532
KW  - Financial markets
KW  - Trade policy
KW  - Panel data
AB  - If protectionist trade policies aim to insure domestic industries against swings in world market prices, the development of financial markets could lead to trade liberalization. Likewise, trade liberalization could lead to the development of financial markets that help agents diversify the added risks. In this paper, we empirically address the hypothesis that there is a positive interdependence between financial development and liberal trade policies. We find a positive and economically significant relationship between the two, with causation running in both directions. The results are, however, somewhat dependent on the measure of trade policy being used.
ER  - 

